1964
01:58:45.606 --> 01:58:49.396
We learned that there's really two main causes that have been identified of this

1965
01:58:49.446 --> 01:58:52.006
type of resistance of minimal residual disease.

1966
01:58:52.046 --> 01:58:56.026
The first is somatic alterations, resistance mutations, which

1967
01:58:56.506 --> 01:58:58.466
themselves can be classified into two groups.

1968
01:58:58.686 --> 01:59:02.046
One are early mutations that arise quickly after starting therapy.

1969
01:59:02.506 --> 01:59:06.086
These are driven by preexisting mutation, preexisting mutant

1970
01:59:06.126 --> 01:59:09.746
clones that are already there. The second is the late

1971
01:59:09.786 --> 01:59:13.116
emerging resistance mutations, and these, as Dr.

1972
01:59:13.306 --> 01:59:17.186
Hoda showed us, are due to adaptive mutagenic mechanisms such

1973
01:59:17.226 --> 01:59:21.026
as those driven by the APOBEC family of enzymes that allow the persister cells

1974
01:59:21.086 --> 01:59:24.146
to continue to accumulate mutations as they are

1975
01:59:24.686 --> 01:59:27.726
being treated with the targeted agents to eventually

1976
01:59:29.586 --> 01:59:32.366
select for a mutation that gives rise to resistance.

1977
01:59:33.006 --> 01:59:36.966
The second dominant type of resistance

1978
01:59:37.006 --> 01:59:40.686
mechanism in this MRD in advanced disease

1979
01:59:40.746 --> 01:59:44.646
is plasticity, cellular plasticity, and this is independent of

1980
01:59:44.666 --> 01:59:48.226
somatic mutations. This is driven by expression changes and

1981
01:59:48.246 --> 01:59:52.106
